<section id="tmthNewReBar" xreflabel="newReBar"><title>newReBar (dialog object method)</title>
<para>
  ReBar objects can not be instantiated by the programmer from Rexx code. Rather a ReBar object is obtained by using the
 <xref linkend="mthNewReBar"/>() method of the <xref linkend="chpDialogObject"/> object. The
  syntax is:
<programlisting>
<![CDATA[
>>-newReBar(--id--)---------------------><

]]>
</programlisting>
</para>
</section>  <!-- End newReBar() [PlainBaseDialog method] -->


<section id="tmthCreateReBar" xreflabel="createReBar"><title>createReBar (UserDialog method)</title>
<para>
  A rebar control can be added to the dialog template for a <xref linkend="clsUserDialog"/> dialog through the <xref
  linkend="mthCreateReBar"/>() method. The basic syntax is:
<programlisting> <![CDATA[
>>--createReBar(-id-,--x-,--y-,--cx-,--cy-+---------+--+-----------------+--)--><
                                          +-,-style-+  +-,-attributeName-+

]]>
</programlisting>
</para>
</section>  <!-- End UserDialog::createReBar() [UserDialog method] -->


<section id="tmthConnectReBarEvent" xreflabel="connectReBarEvent"><title>connectReBarEvent (dialog object method)</title>
<para>
  To connect event notifications from a rebar control use the
 <xref linkend="mthConnectReBarEvent"/>() method of the
  <xref linkend="chpDialogObject"/> object. The basic syntax is:

<programlisting> <![CDATA[
>>-connectReBarEvent(--id--,--event--+----------------+--+--------------+--)----><
                                       +--,-methodName--+  +-,-willReply--+

]]>
</programlisting>
</para>
</section>  <!-- End connectReBarEvent() [EventNotification method] -->

